In a bowl, combine the first seven ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until serving. In another bowl, combine the paprika, onion powder, salt and cayenne; rub over both sides of fillets. Grill, covered, in a grill basket coated with nonstick cooking spray over medium-hot heat, or broil 6 inch from the heat for 5-6 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve with lemon wedges and yogurt sauce.